A vintage 1970s advertisement-style illustration of a living room scene showing a small white electronic set-top box sitting on a retro wooden TV console, surrounded by a graveyard of identical but slightly older, yellowed versions of the same box stacked haphazardly in the corner. The scene has warm amber and avocado green tones typical of 70s interior design, with shag carpet and wood paneling. A single spotlight dramatically illuminates the newest pristine white box like a prized possession, while dust motes float in the beam. The mood is simultaneously celebratory and darkly humorous, suggesting forced obsolescence dressed up as progress.
